From Thomas Trusk Subject re GeoSphere Image In article ryan malayter writes Does anyone know if a digitized version of the GeoSphere image is available via ftp For those of you who don't know it is a composite photograph of the entire earth with cloudcover I just think it's really It was created with government funds and sattelites as a research project so I would assume it's in the public Thanks for any info Ryan I have a copy of 'The Earth From Space' on my wall that I purchased from Space Shots LA CA As printed on the poster the image was created by Tom Van Sant and the GeoSphere The image IS copyrighted so I doubt that you'll find it legally in the public Part of the proceeds from the sale of the image go to the GeoSphere Project an environmental education thing and the cost is nominal so crack a and buy one Also I don't think it's always safe to assume that just because the government 'funded' a project any products will be provided for Many government agencies NASA NOAA and some private groups National Geographic provided assistance to the GeoSphere This collaboration seems to be mostly oriented to educating the public rather than pure Thomas Trusk of Cellular Biology Anatomy Email to Medical College of Wisconsin Milwaukee WI DISCLAIMER I have no affiliation with any of the above mentioned This is just my opinion not a flame or Where am I Who turned off the lights What's that funny noise I feel